# Example environment for agent-assisted development tooling.
#
# These variables are read from the shell environment by the agent tooling
# (review-paths, take-bestiary, the handle-ticket / design-review skills, etc.).
# This file is documentation only — nothing sources it automatically. Export the
# variables from your shell profile or sandbox configuration to take effect.

# VAULT_BASE — the agent workspace inside your Obsidian vault. Review reports,
# design-review findings, and screenshot catalogs are written under here (e.g.
# $VAULT_BASE/Reviews, $VAULT_BASE/screenshots). When unset, the tooling falls
# back to the maintainer's conventional layout, ~/obsidian/protospy/Claude.
VAULT_BASE=$HOME/obsidian/protospy/Claude

# OBSIDIAN_REVIEWS — optional, overrides only the review-report base directory
# (otherwise $VAULT_BASE/Reviews). Set this if reviews live outside VAULT_BASE.
# OBSIDIAN_REVIEWS=$HOME/obsidian/protospy/Claude/Reviews
